  0. Additional Definitions.

  As used herein, "this License" refers to version 3 of the GNU Lesser
General Public License, and the "GNU GPL" refers to version 3 of the GNU
General Public License.

  "The Library" refers to a covered work governed by this License,
other than an Application or a Combined Work as defined below.

  An "Application" is any work that makes use of an interface provided
by the Library, but which is not otherwise based on the Library.
Defining a subclass of a class defined by the Library is deemed a mode
of using an interface provided by the Library.

  A "Combined Work" is a work produced by combining or linking an
Application with the Library, with respect to some of the Library's
valid combining modes. A Combined Work need not contain anything that
is separately distributeable.

  "Corresponding Source" for a Combined Work means object code
and/or source form of the Combined Work, including any data and
utility programs needed for reproducing the Combined Work from the
Library, excluding the System Libraries of the Combined Work in
executable form.

  "Corresponding Source" for a Combined Work means the Corresponding
Source for the Combined Work, excluding any source code for portions
of the Combined Work that, considered in isolation, are based on the
Application.

  "Required Materials" means the Corresponding Source for the
Combined Work that is not an Application and is not a System Library.

  " Covered Work" means either the Application or a Combined Work.

